== Berlin.pm

+* Meetings since 2002
+* 118 Mailing list subscribers
+* 8-10 people on average at meetings
+* We usually do only social meetings
+* But we organized the German Perl Workshop 2013!
+* We try to meet at a new location every month
+* A history of all our meetings on a map can be found here:
   http://berlin.pm.org/history_map.html

----
== perl-community.de

+* Started around 2003
+* Board was running previously on perl.de, but the domain was sold to
   someone wanting to make money with it, so we got our own domain and
   moved the whole community there
+* The number of threads is decreasing =( but this seems to happen to
   other perl boards too
+* Board is running on perl with a software created by me and community
   members.


----
== perl-community.de Software

+* It has a couple of nice features (I think!)
+* Threads are trees (like on reddit or perlmonks)
+* You can immediately see which thread messages you haven't read yet
+* Headlines in a thread are colored by age
+* Navigating in a long thread is easy with a navigator item on the left
+* Uses some javascript, but usable without
+* It's fast!
+* Unfortunately it's a hell to install because of lack of documentation
    and utilities

